  "text": "a. The liver transplant candidate with HCC and portal hypertension but no liver decompensation. There has only been one published study of interferon-free antiviral therapy in this situation. Curry et al. reported on using sofosbuvir and ribavarin in 61 patients awaiting liver transplantation for HCC as the primary indication [CITATION_1] . The majority of patients had HCV GT-1. Patients had CPS \\ 7. Nine patients relapsed, did not respond or had viral breakthrough whilst 47 underwent liver transplantation. Of these, 3 had HCV detected at transplant and all 3 relapsed post-transplant. Forty-three patients were PCR negative at transplant and 10 relapsed post-transplant. The authors claimed that 24/25 patients who had the virus not detected for [4 weeks and underwent transplant had no recurrence. Thus, it seems that 30/61 patents (49 %)",
